In lists.linux.kernel, you wrote:
> I am interested in writing a Linux driver for the remote control
> interface included on some Hauppauge WinTV video capture cards.
> Before I get started I wanted to ask the usual questions.  Does this
> already exist (am I just missing something)?  Is someone already working
> on this project?  If I start the project tomorrow will someone already
> have it finished before I make any progress?
Lirc does this.
Homepage:
  
http://fsinfo.cs.uni-sb.de/
%7Ecolumbus/lirc/
latest software:
  
http://fsinfo.cs.uni-sb.de/
%7Ecolumbus/lirc/software/snapshots/
A driver for Hauppauge remotes comes with bttv.  You'll have to download
the separate version from 
http://me.in-berlin.de/~kraxel/v4l/
 because it
isn't in the standard kernel.  The driver will probably moved to the lirc
package in near future.
  Gerd
